<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="memset" id="memset">memset</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstring&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">void</span><span class="sy2">*</span> <span class="kw3">memset</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">void</span><span class="sy2">*</span> dest, <span class="kw4">int</span> ch, <span class="kw4">size_t</span> count <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
Fills a memory buffer with a byte value. This function is optimized and is faster than filling the same array using <code>for</code> loop.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "memset" [1-250] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit2"><a name="parameters" id="parameters">Parameters</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

<code>dest</code> - pointer to the start of the buffer to fill
</p>

<p>
<code>ch</code> - byte value to fill
</p>

<p>
<code>count</code> - number of bytes to write
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT2 SECTION "Parameters" [251-392] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit3"><a name="return_value" id="return_value">Return value</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

<code>dest</code>
</p>

</div>
